Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high. Bring a #medium pot{} of
@salt{} water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Mince @chives{} and @parsley{}.
Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Trim and halve @zucchini{1}(halved lengthwise);
slice crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Halve @demi-baguette{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @ricotta cheese{4%ounce}, half the chives and
parsley, a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Place
2 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon} in a separate small microwave-safe bowl; microwave
until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in a pinch of garlic to taste; season with
salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat
(use a large pan for 4 servings). Add zucchini; cook, stirring occasionally,
until browned and tender, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add remaining garlic; cook until
fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper; transfer to a #plate{}.
Meanwhile, add @gnocchi{8.8%ounce} to pot of boiling water. Cook until tender,
~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for zucchini over medium heat. Pour in
@marinara cup{14%ounce}; bring to a simmer.

> TIP: Be careful—sauce may splatter.

Stir in cooked gnocchi, 1 TBSP plain butter, and a pinch of salt and pepper. If
needed, stir in reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until gnocchi
is coated in sauce.

> TIP: If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a baking dish.

Scatter zucchini over gnocchi mixture, then sprinkle with
@mozzarella cheese{½%cup}. Broil until cheese is bubbly and lightly browned,
~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from oven; let cool slightly. Meanwhile, place baguette
halves on a #baking sheet{}; brush cut sides with garlic butter. Broil on top
rack until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Halve garlic bread on a diagonal. Dollop baked gnocchi with herby ricotta.
Sprinkle with remaining chives and parsley. Serve straight from the pan (or dish)
with garlic bread on the side.